OL,3,CWelsh researchers develop new test for
OL,4,Cthe most common cancer amongst men
OL,6,FIn the UK, more than 52,000 men are
OL,7,Fdiagnosed with prostate cancer every
OL,8,Fyear, and up to one-in-four of these
OL,9,Fare diagnosed at a later stage of the
OL,10,Fdisease, requiring more extensive
OL,11,Ftreatments. The cost to the NHS for
OL,12,Fextensive treatments alone is #650
OL,13,Fmillion.
OL,15,FProstate cancer is the second most
OL,16,Fcommon cause of cancer death in men in
OL,17,Fthe UK, with around 12,000 deaths
OL,18,Fevery year.
OL,20,FProstate cancer - in numbers
